        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 3:18PM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 317 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 12 miles northeast of Darby to 24 miles
southwest of Philipsburg to 22 miles southwest of West Valley.
Movement was northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Skalkaho Pass, Georgetown, and Porters Corner.
</description>
        <instruction>These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
